01/31/79  expand_symbols, esb

Syntax:  esb input_path {output_path}


Function: takes an input text segment containing Speedtype symbols
    and expands it using the options and symbols defined in the current
    Speedtype symbol dictionary.


Arguments: 
input_path
   is the pathname of the input text segment.
output_path
   is an optional pathname of an output text segment. If this control argument
   is not specified, the original contents of input_path are overwritten with
   expanded material.
